MEC Kwazi Mshengu says the expulsions are part of efforts to cleanse the department. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN – The KwaZulu-Natal Education Department says it is intensifying the war against sex pests who are preying on pupils. The department has axed seven teachers and an administrator, for sexual violations against pupils. KZN Education MEC Kwazi Mshengu says the expulsions are part of efforts to cleanse the department. “As the department, we signed letters of expulsion for seven educators last week and these cases came about as a result from parents including learners who complained of sexual harassment to the department,” Mshengu said. READ: Sex pest teachers to be named, to alert communities Mshengu has expressed concern about the length of time the cases will take. Mshengu says he has about 12 appeals that have been brought to his attention.